<body>
    <h1>Privacy Policy for SizeCard</h1>
    <p><strong>Last Updated: September 29, 2025</strong></p>
    
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>Welcome to SizeCard. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our mobile application.</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>

<h3>Personal Information</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Account Information: Name, email address, phone number (optional)</li>
    <li>Profile Data: Gender, age, relationship information</li>
    <li>Sizing Information: Clothing measurements and preferences</li>
    <li>Family Member Information: Names and sizing information for family members you add</li>
    <li>Share Codes: Unique 6-character codes for sharing sizing cards</li>
</ul>

<h3>Usage Data</h3>
<ul>
    <li>App Usage: Features used, time spent in app, interactions</li>
    <li>Device Information: iOS version, device model, app version</li>
    <li>Performance Data: Crash reports, error logs, app performance metrics</li>
    <li>Analytics Data: User behavior patterns and feature usage</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>

<h3>Core App Functionality</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Account Management: Create and maintain your user account</li>
    <li>Sizing Cards: Store and organize your clothing measurements</li>
    <li>Family Sharing: Share sizing information with family members</li>
    <li>Deep Linking: Enable sharing of sizing cards via links</li>
</ul>

<h3>Communication</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Notifications: Send updates about sizing changes and app features</li>
    <li>Email Communications: Welcome emails, subscription confirmations, password resets</li>
    <li>Support: Respond to your inquiries and provide customer service</li>
</ul>

<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>We use the following third-party services:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Firebase (Google): Authentication, database, cloud functions, crashlytics</li>
    <li>RevenueCat: Subscription management and payment processing</li>
    <li>Apple Services: App Store, Keychain, push notifications</li>
    <li>Expo: Development platform and analytics</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data Security</h2>
<p>We implement industry-standard security measures:</p>
<ul>
    <li>AES-256 encryption for sensitive data</li>
    <li>HTTPS with certificate pinning</li>
    <li>iOS Keychain with biometric protection</li>
    <li>Firebase security rules and access controls</li>
    <li>Regular security audits and updates</li>
</ul>

<h2>User Rights</h2>
<p>You have the right to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Access your personal information</li>
    <li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
    <li>Export your sizing data</li>
    <li>Delete your account and data</li>
    <li>Opt-out of marketing communications</li>
    <li>Manage notification preferences</li>
</ul>

<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>SizeCard is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.</p>

<h2>Data Retention</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Account data is retained while your account is active</li>
    <li>Data is automatically deleted after 365 days of inactivity</li>
    <li>All data is deleted within 30 days of account closure</li>
</ul>

<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes through the app or email.</p>

<h2>Contact Information</h2>
<p>For privacy inquiries or support:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Email: sizecardhelp@gmail.com</li>
    <li>Response Time: 24-48 hours</li>
</ul>

<p><em>This Privacy Policy complies with GDPR, CCPA, Apple App Store Guidelines, and COPPA.</em></p>
    
</body>
